# Workers KV

KV is a globally distributed key-value store for Cloudflare Workers. It's optimized for read-heavy workloads — reads are fast everywhere, writes are eventually consistent (up to 60s propagation).

## Setup

### Create a KV Namespace

```bash
# Create namespace
wrangler kv namespace create MY_KV
# Output: Add the following to wrangler.toml:
# [[kv_namespaces]]
# binding = "MY_KV"
# id = "abc123..."

# Create preview namespace (for wrangler dev)
wrangler kv namespace create MY_KV --preview
```

### wrangler.toml

```toml
[[kv_namespaces]]
binding = "MY_KV"
id = "abc123def456"           # production namespace ID
preview_id = "789ghi012"      # preview namespace ID (for wrangler dev)
```

## Worker API

```typescript
export interface Env {
  MY_KV: KVNamespace;
}

export default {
  async fetch(request: Request, env: Env): Promise<Response> {
    // PUT — write a value
    await env.MY_KV.put('user:123', JSON.stringify({ name: 'Alice', role: 'admin' }));

    // PUT with TTL (seconds) — auto-expires
    await env.MY_KV.put('session:abc', 'token-data', { expirationTtl: 3600 });

    // PUT with expiration (unix timestamp)
    await env.MY_KV.put('temp:xyz', 'data', { expiration: 1735689600 });

    // PUT with metadata
    await env.MY_KV.put('doc:1', 'content', {
      metadata: { author: 'agent', version: 2 },
    });

    // GET — read a value
    const value = await env.MY_KV.get('user:123');           // string | null
    const json = await env.MY_KV.get('user:123', 'json');    // parsed JSON
    const buf = await env.MY_KV.get('binary:1', 'arrayBuffer');
    const stream = await env.MY_KV.get('large:1', 'stream'); // ReadableStream

    // GET with metadata
    const { value: val, metadata } = await env.MY_KV.getWithMetadata('doc:1', 'text');

    // DELETE
    await env.MY_KV.delete('session:abc');

    // LIST — enumerate keys
    const listed = await env.MY_KV.list({ prefix: 'user:', limit: 100 });
    // listed.keys = [{ name: 'user:123', expiration?, metadata? }, ...]
    // listed.list_complete = true/false
    // listed.cursor = '...' (for pagination)

    // Paginated listing
    let cursor: string | undefined;
    const allKeys: string[] = [];
    do {
      const result = await env.MY_KV.list({ prefix: 'user:', limit: 1000, cursor });
      allKeys.push(...result.keys.map(k => k.name));
      cursor = result.list_complete ? undefined : result.cursor;
    } while (cursor);

    return Response.json({ keys: allKeys });
  },
};
```

## CLI Operations

```bash
# Write a value
wrangler kv key put --namespace-id abc123 "my-key" "my-value"

# Read a value
wrangler kv key get --namespace-id abc123 "my-key"

# Delete a value
wrangler kv key delete --namespace-id abc123 "my-key"

# List keys
wrangler kv key list --namespace-id abc123 --prefix "user:"

# Bulk put from JSON file
wrangler kv bulk put --namespace-id abc123 data.json
# data.json: [{"key":"k1","value":"v1"},{"key":"k2","value":"v2"}]

# Bulk delete
wrangler kv bulk delete --namespace-id abc123 keys.json
# keys.json: ["k1", "k2"]
```

## REST API

```bash
# List namespaces
curl "https://api.cloudflare.com/client/v4/accounts/$ACCOUNT_ID/storage/kv/namespaces" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN"

# Write a value
curl -X PUT "https://api.cloudflare.com/client/v4/accounts/$ACCOUNT_ID/storage/kv/namespaces/$NAMESPACE_ID/values/my-key" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN" \
  --data "my-value"

# Read a value
curl "https://api.cloudflare.com/client/v4/accounts/$ACCOUNT_ID/storage/kv/namespaces/$NAMESPACE_ID/values/my-key" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN"
```

## Consistency Model

KV is **eventually consistent**. After a write, the new value propagates to all edge locations within 60 seconds. Reads from the same location that performed the write are immediately consistent. This makes KV ideal for:
- Configuration that changes infrequently
- Feature flags
- Cached API responses
- Static content

KV is **not** suitable for:
- Counters or incrementing values (use Durable Objects instead)
- Real-time collaboration state
- Financial transactions
